<Layout
	title="About"
	description="About Ugo Giordano"
>
	<p>
		I'm Ugo Giordano, a software engineer at Red Hat on the OpenShift AI (RHOAI)
		platform team, where I focus on the security side of the platform. I have a PhD
		in computer engineering from Università degli Studi di Napoli Federico II,
		where I researched reliability and availability of critical systems, focusing on
		Network Function Virtualization (NFV) and Software Defined Networks (SDN). During
		that work I contributed to Nokia Bell Labs' NetUnix project and co-authored papers
		on SDN control plane performance testing and static analysis prioritization.
	</p>
	<p>
		At Red Hat I work across the Kubernetes and AI/ML stack. I'm a certified
		OpenShift administrator and Kubernetes specialist. My day-to-day involves
		Go, Python, TypeScript and the cloud-native toolchain: Podman, Buildah,
		Skopeo, Istio, OpenShift. Beyond security, I spend a lot of time building
		tools that make engineering workflows faster and less manual. I'm particularly
		interested in how AI integrates into real developer tooling, not as a chatbot
		but as an agent that can actually do things.
	</p>
	<p>
		Before the PhD I competed in the International Olympiad in Informatics. These
		days I care about security, reliability, testing and building things that
		actually work in production.
	</p>
	<p>
